# Deployment Runbook

Production deployment execution guide for [PROJECT_NAME].

## Current Status
- Phase: 3 (Server Deployment Readiness)
- Production cutover: [NOT_STARTED/IN_PROGRESS/READY]

## Preconditions
- [ ] Feature scope for release is complete and documented
- [ ] Verify gate passes on release candidate
- [ ] Backup and restore process validated
- [ ] Required environment variables validated
- [ ] Security posture checklist reviewed

## Environment Baseline
- Host OS hardened and access policy enforced
- Runtime installed and healthy
- External routing/tunnel config validated
- Secrets provided via environment/secret manager only

## Deployment Steps
1. Pull latest code on target host.
2. Ensure environment values are present and valid.
3. Start/update runtime stack.
4. Initialize/migrate DB as needed.
5. Verify service status.
6. Validate key workflows.

## Post-Deploy Validation
- [ ] Service status healthy
- [ ] Logs contain no critical startup errors
- [ ] Auth and critical workflows succeed
- [ ] No unintended public write endpoints
- [ ] Automated verify/smoke checks pass where applicable

## Rollback Procedure
1. Stop current release.
2. Re-deploy prior known-good image/tag/commit.
3. Restore DB from latest validated backup if needed.
4. Re-run smoke checks.

